cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with denoising of signals corrupted by a discrete memoryless channel, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the implementation and complexity of the denoiser, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.MM). The paper also presents an estimator for the subset of feasible channels, which involves statistical inference and data analysis (cs.DS, cs.SI).
